      "name": "Mesh Independence Study — GCI Assessment",
      "description": "Three systematically refined meshes (1.1M, 2.8M, and 4.2M polyhedral elements) were evaluated. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for NIH was 4.7%, 2.1%, and the extrapolated value agreed with the fine-mesh result to within 0.4%. The 4.2M mesh was selected for all subsequent simulations.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/mesh-independence-study-2023"
